In article <BznFDu.5uI@cs.bham.ac.uk>, jwh@cs.bham.ac.uk (James Hawtin) writes:
|> Ok so I understand now how the RSA system works, I am sure others have already asked
|> but what is the best way to attack it?

If you can arrange to deliver ciphertext and see the decrypted plaintext,
I have heard it said that a ciphertext frame of ...00002 will show up the
private key nicely.  I think one can work out a test of this with small keys.

Moral:  Don't decrypt such a frame! 
